  "prompt": "How do you know if a guy is obsessed with you?",
  "response": "Determining if someone is obsessed with you can be complex, as it involves a range of emotional and behavioral indicators. Here are some signs that might suggest a person is overly fixated on you:\n\n1. **Constant Communication**: They message, call, or reach out to you excessively, even when you don't respond immediately or show interest.\n\n2. **Over-Involvement**: They want to be involved in every aspect of your life, including your personal, professional, and social activities.\n\n3. **Boundary Issues**: They disregard your boundaries or become upset if you set limitations on your interactions.\n\n4. **Jealousy and Possessiveness**: They exhibit strong jealousy and possessiveness, often without reasonable cause, and may try to control who you interact with.\n\n5. **Unwanted Attention**: They give you excessive attention, gifts, or compliments, even when you've expressed discomfort or asked them to stop.\n\n6. **Stalking Behavior**: They follow or watch you without your knowledge, try to track your location, or show up unexpectedly where they know you will be.\n\n7. **Preoccupation**: They are excessively preoccupied with you and make you the central focus of their thoughts and actions.\n\n8. **Pressure for Immediate Response**: They demand immediate replies and can become upset if you don\u2019t respond quickly.\n\n9. **Isolation**: They attempt to isolate you from friends and family, wanting you to depend on them entirely.\n\n10. **Unwarranted Anger**: They become angry or disappointed if you don\u2019t reciprocate their level of interest or affection.\n\nIf you feel uncomfortable or unsafe due to someone's behavior, it is important to take steps to protect yourself. Communicate your boundaries clearly, and if necessary, seek support from friends, family, or professional resources such as counselors. In severe cases, consider legal measures such as restraining orders.",
